# Docs & Rules Sync Convention

Whenever you modify code under `apps/`, `packages/`, or `infra/`, you MUST also review and update the following files if the change affects behavior, data flow, endpoints, DB schema, or architectural patterns:

- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` – processing flow, sequence diagram, component descriptions, endpoint list.
- `docs/PROJECT_CONTEXT.md` – product flow, engine descriptions, roadmap items.
- `docs/DATABASE-SCHEMA.md` – models, enums, relations, migration notes.
- `.cursor/rules/pension-architecture.mdc` – architecture principles, feature design patterns, data/schema rules.

## When to update

- New or changed API endpoint → update `ARCHITECTURE.md` (endpoint list + sequence diagram).
- New or changed worker pipeline step → update `ARCHITECTURE.md` (processing flow section).
- New or changed Prisma model/enum/field → update `DATABASE-SCHEMA.md` and `ARCHITECTURE.md`.
- New engine or package (projection, simulation, tasks, rules) → update `PROJECT_CONTEXT.md` and `ARCHITECTURE.md`.
- New architectural pattern or responsibility shift → update `.cursor/rules/pension-architecture.mdc`.

## How to update

- Keep docs concise and factual; match the existing style of each file.
- Update mermaid diagrams (sequence, ER, flowchart) when the flow they depict changes.
- Do NOT remove information about unchanged parts; only add or revise what changed.
- Do the doc updates in the same response as the code change, not as a separate follow-up.
